                           <div class="entire_tip">
<div class="tip_number">TIP 155</div>
<div class="tip_contents">
            Irregular-shaped, dark, multicolored, enlarging, bleeding, itching, or painful moles need to be frequently checked for early detection of malignant melanoma. Early treatment can be life-saving. Being seen within days or a couple of weeks is much better than within months. The sooner, the better.
        </div>

</div>
